\title{Glass Hopping}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{trit}{0}

\meta{description}{"Glass Bead Game + World Hopping via Observational Bridge Types. Navigate possibility space through ordered locale ≪ relations with Narya-verified transitions."}

\subtree{
\title{Glass Hopping: Observational Bridge Navigation}
\blockquote{*"The bead connects. The bridge directs. The hop observes."*}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{\strong{Glass Hopping} synthesizes three skills into one:}

\pre{\startverb
| Skill | Contribution | Type-Theoretic Role |
|-------|--------------|---------------------|
| **glass-bead-game** | Conceptual connections (beads) | Objects in frame |
| **world-hopping** | Possibility navigation (hops) | Morphisms between worlds |
| **ordered-locale** | Directional structure (≪) | Bridge types |
\stopverb}

\p{The key insight: \strong{World hops are bridge types in an ordered locale}.}

\pre{\startverb
Bead₁ ────Bridge(B₁, B₂)────→ Bead₂
  │                              │
  ↓ observational               ↓
World₁ ←────U ≪ V────→ World₂
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Observational Bridge = Hop}
\p{A \strong{hop} from world W₁ to W₂ is an \strong{observational bridge type}:}

\pre{\startverb
def Hop (W₁ W₂ : World) : Type := Bridge W₁ W₂
\stopverb}

\p{The bridge is:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Directed}: W₁ ≪ W₂ (not symmetric like HoTT paths)}
\li{\strong{Observational}: Equality up to observable behavior}
\li{\strong{Verifiable}: Type-checked by Narya}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Glass Beads as Opens}
\p{Each \strong{bead} corresponds to an \strong{open} in the ordered locale:}

\pre{\startverb
class GlassBead:
    domain: str          # mathematics, music, philosophy
    concept: str         # The conceptual content
    open_set: FrozenSet  # Points in the locale where bead is "active"
    trit: int            # GF(3) polarity: -1, 0, +1
\stopverb}

\p{The frame of opens forms a \strong{complete Heyting algebra}:}

\ul{
\li{Meet (∧): Bead intersection (shared concepts)}
\li{Join (∨): Bead union (combined concepts)  }
\li{Implication (→): Bead entailment}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Triangle Inequality via ≪ Order}
\p{The Badiou triangle inequality is \strong{automatically satisfied} by the ≪ order:}

\pre{\startverb
If U ≪ V and V ≪ W, then U ≪ W (transitivity)
\stopverb}

\p{Distance becomes \strong{bridge composition length}:}

\pre{\startverb
def bridge_distance(W1, W2, locale):
    """Distance = minimum bridge chain length"""
    # Find shortest path in ≪ graph
    opens = [U for U in locale.frame.carrier if W1.active_in(U)]
    for U in opens:
        for V in locale.frame.carrier:
            if locale.order_ll(U, V) and W2.active_in(V):
                return 1  # Direct bridge exists
    return float('inf')  # No bridge path
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Glass Hopping Game}
\subtree{
\title{Setup}
\pre{\startverb
game = GlassHoppingGame(
    locale=triadic_gf3(),  # Ordered locale for structure
    seed=0x42D,            # Deterministic randomness
    players=3              # Triadic (GF(3) conserved)
)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Moves}
\subtree{
\title{1. PLACE: Add Bead to Locale}
\pre{\startverb
move = GlassHop.Place(
    bead=Bead(domain="mathematics", concept="prime"),
    open_set=frozenset([1]),  # Active in the "plus" region
    trit=+1
)
# Creates: Open in frame with bead attached
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. BRIDGE: Create ≪ Connection}
\pre{\startverb
move = GlassHop.Bridge(
    from_bead=bead_prime,
    to_bead=bead_harmony,
    bridge_type="harmonic_series"  # Primes → overtones
)
# Creates: WayBelow relation in ordered locale
# Verifies: Open cone condition
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. HOP: Navigate via Bridge}
\pre{\startverb
move = GlassHop.Hop(
    from_world=current_world,
    via_bridge=bridge_prime_harmony,
    to_world=target_world
)
# Executes: Badiou event along bridge
# Preserves: GF(3) conservation
# Validates: Triangle inequality
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. OBSERVE: Collapse Superposition}
\pre{\startverb
move = GlassHop.Observe(
    world=superposed_world,
    observable=bead_measurement
)
# Collapses: Multiple possible states to one
# Bridge type: Observational equality witness
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scoring}
\pre{\startverb
| Move | Points | Bridge Bonus | GF(3) Bonus |
|------|--------|--------------|-------------|
| PLACE | 10 | — | ×2 if balances |
| BRIDGE | 25 | ×2 if ≪ verified | ×3 if cone-preserving |
| HOP | 50 | ×(1/distance) | ×2 if conserved |
| OBSERVE | 30 | ×2 if unique | — |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Elegance}: Shorter bridge chains score higher.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Narya Type Theory}
\subtree{
\title{World as Type}
\pre{\startverb
def World : Type := sig (
  seed : Nat,
  epoch : Nat,
  state : State,
  invariants : List Invariant
)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Bead as Subtype}
\pre{\startverb
def Bead (W : World) : Type := sig (
  domain : Domain,
  concept : String,
  active : W .state → Prop
)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Bridge as Directed Path}
\pre{\startverb
def GlassHop (W₁ W₂ : World) (B₁ : Bead W₁) (B₂ : Bead W₂) : Type := sig (
  bridge : Bridge W₁ W₂,
  bead_transfer : (x : W₁ .state) → B₁ .active x → B₂ .active (transport bridge x),
  trit_conserved : trit B₁ + trit B₂ + trit bridge ≡ 0 (mod 3)
)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Open Cone Condition}
\pre{\startverb
def OpenConeCondition (L : OrderedLocale) (U : Open L) : Type := sig (
  up_is_open : IsOpen L (up_closure L U),
  down_is_open : IsOpen L (down_closure L U)
)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Triangle Inequality}
\pre{\startverb
def TriangleInequality (W₁ W₂ W₃ : World) 
  (h₁₂ : GlassHop W₁ W₂) (h₂₃ : GlassHop W₂ W₃) : Type :=
  sig (
    composed : GlassHop W₁ W₃,
    distance_bound : distance composed ≤ distance h₁₂ + distance h₂₃
  )
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Conservation}
\p{Each glass hop preserves the triadic invariant:}

\pre{\startverb
Σ trits = trit(bead₁) + trit(bridge) + trit(bead₂) ≡ 0 (mod 3)
\stopverb}

